RRS was a simple and sensitive method to study nanoparticles and was chosen for the CDs. The RRS spectra of CDUN was investigated, there were three RRS peaks at 290 nm, 410 nm and 480 nm (Fig. 8
                        ). As the concentration of CDUN increased, the former characteristic peak of the carbon dots gradually increased, and was selected for use. The prepared CDUN was put at room temperature for several days, to examine the stability. The maximum absorption peak (A350nm) of the carbon dots was measured at different time. It turned out that, the RRS spectral data was I290nm, the fluorescence spectral data was F450 nm and the relative standard deviation (RSD) was within 10% (Table 1
                        ), which show that the prepared carbon dots were more stable.

The influence of pH of BS, concentration of BS, CDN and of Apt on fluorescence signal of the system were investigated respectively (Fig. 12
                        ). According to the fluorescence characteristics of CDUN, the fluorescence peak at 450 nm was observed at λ
                        ex = 370 nm. BS with different pH were respectively added to investigate the fluorescence signal. The value of fluorescence signal changed most when BS with a pH of 4 was added, therefore BS with a pH of 4 was selected. Different concentration gradient of BS at pH 4 were respectively added to investigate the fluorescence signal. The value of fluorescence signal changed most when 10 mmoL/L of DSP-CA BS with a pH of 4 was added, therefore BS with a pH of 4 was selected. Different concentration of CDUN solution were respectively added to investigate the fluorescence signal. According to Fig. 12, the value of fluorescence signal changed most when 20 mg/L of CDUN solution was added, therefore 20 mg/L of CDUN solution was selected. Different concentration of Apt solution was respectively added to investigate the fluorescence signal. The value of fluorescence signal changed most when 0.08 μmoL/L of Apt solution was added, therefore 0.08 μmoL/L of Apt solution was selected.

Under the best conditions, the relationship between the concentration of K+ and its corresponding ΔF was obtained (Table 2
                        , Figs. S21–S25). In the five systems of Apt-BS-CD0/CDUN/CDTN/CDCN/CDAN-K+, the slope of working curve ΔF in CDUN system was the largest, therefore CDUN system was the most sensitive. It could be applied on the fluorescent detection of 0.03–0.27 μmoL/L of K+ with a linear equation of ΔF = 921.1c+17.6, a coefficient of 0.9844 and a detection limit (DL) of 0.67 nmoL/L. Under the best conditions for obtaining biggest value of ΔI = ΔF+ΔIRRS, the relationship between the concentration of K+ and its corresponding ΔF, ΔIRRS and the dual-mode (ΔI) were obtained (Fig. 13
                        ). In the system of Apt-BS-CDUN-K+, the slope of working curve of di-mode was the largest, therefore the CDUN di-mode system was the most sensitive. It could be applied on the detection of 0.008–0.27 μmoL/L of K+ with a linear equation of ΔI = 2264.8c+4.1, a coefficient of 0.9971 and a DL of 0.3 nmoL/L. Compared with the reported spectral method for the determination of K+ [46–50] (Table 3
                        ), this method was simpler and more sensitive.
